{"id":736649,"url":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tufts_University","text":"Tufts University is a private research university in Medford and Somerville, Massachusetts. It was founded in 1852 by Christian universalists.\nIt was a small New England liberal arts college until its transformation into a larger research university in the 1970s. It is known for its internationalism and study abroad programs.","categories":[],"infobox_types":[],"annotations":[{"uri":"Private_university","surface_form":"private","offset":22},{"uri":"Research_university","surface_form":"research university","offset":30},{"uri":"Medford%2C_Massachusetts","surface_form":"Medford","offset":53},{"uri":"Somerville%2C_Massachusetts","surface_form":"Somerville, Massachusetts","offset":65},{"uri":"Christian_universalism","surface_form":"Christian universalists","offset":118},{"uri":"New_England","surface_form":"New England","offset":158},{"uri":"Liberal_arts","surface_form":"liberal arts","offset":170},{"uri":"Internationalism_(politics)","surface_form":"internationalism","offset":284},{"uri":"Study_abroad","surface_form":"study abroad","offset":305}]}